  "texts": [
    "Within the TFDR repository, the Codes folder contains Python scripts used for NER, KSR, and RE baseline experiments.",
    "The Corpus directory includes a ProcData subfolder, where the preprocessed datasets for these experiments are stored; each dataset is in a tab-separated text file format without column headings.",
    "Additionally, the RawData subfolder within the Corpus directory holds the original corpus files, formatted in an extended version of the PubTator corpus structure.",
    "This format includes three main sections: Text, NER, and RE information, organized as depicted in Fig. 3, with all data tab-separated.",
    "In the Text information segment, the paper's title, abstract, and key-sentences are differentiated by the |t|, |a|, and |k| tags, respectively."
  ],
